What This Is
The Scheduling & Communication Pod is the career management backbone of the Folio platform. It handles everything that happens after a candidate discovers an opportunity â€” tracking applications, scheduling interviews, managing recruiter relationships, logging follow-ups, and enabling direct candidate-recruiter communication.
Think of it as a personal CRM for your job search, built as a production-ready REST API.

API Overview
Show Image
26 endpoints across 5 core modules, fully documented via Swagger at /docs.

Modules
Application Lifecycle
Track every application from submission to final decision.
GET    /api/v1/applications
POST   /api/v1/applications
GET    /api/v1/applications/{id}
POST   /api/v1/applications/{id}/status
Pipeline: Applied â†’ Viewed â†’ Under Review â†’ Shortlisted â†’ Interview Scheduled â†’ Selected â†’ Rejected

Interview Scheduling
Schedule, reschedule, and cancel interviews with full activity logging.
GET    /api/v1/interviews
GET    /api/v1/applications/{id}/interview
POST   /api/v1/applications/{id}/interviews
PUT    /api/v1/applications/{id}/interviews
POST   /api/v1/applications/{id}/interviews/cancel
Supports online and offline formats. Every action auto-logs a confirmation activity.

Calendar Availability
Candidate submits available slots. Recruiter confirms one. Interview is created automatically.
POST   /api/v1/applications/{id}/availability
GET    /api/v1/applications/{id}/availability
POST   /api/v1/applications/{id}/availability/confirm

Candidate â†” Recruiter Messaging
Threaded conversations tied to specific applications. Every message triggers a notification activity.
POST   /api/v1/conversations
GET    /api/v1/conversations/{id}
POST   /api/v1/conversations/{id}/messages
GET    /api/v1/conversations/{id}/messages

Activities, Notifications & Action Items
Every event in the system is logged as an activity record.
GET    /api/v1/activities
POST   /api/v1/applications/{id}/activities
PATCH  /api/v1/activities/{id}
GET    /api/v1/notifications
GET    /api/v1/action-items
POST   /api/v1/applications/{id}/tasks
POST   /api/v1/applications/{id}/follow-ups

